Consent_1:
Information 

 

Study Name: Social Attitudes in Your Area

 

Welcome, and thank you for choosing to participate in our study.

 

This 25 minute online survey is being carried out by a PhD candidate, Sam Taylor (supervised by Professor Greg Maio), and will ask you several questions about your own attitudes, thoughts and behaviours and your views on the attitudes, thoughts and behaviours of others in the area that you live.

 

Ethics: At the end of the study, we will inform you in more detail about the aims and hypotheses of this study and give you the opportunity to provide feedback. Should you have any questions or wish to withdraw your data from the study at this stage, you may do so by emailing sjt80@bath.ac.uk within two weeks of completing the study and quoting your Prolific ID. You may also withdraw at any time by closing your browser window; any data collected up until that point will be deleted by the researchers. If you have any additional questions, please do not hesitate to contact the researchers (details below).

 

Eligibility requirements: You must be over 18 years of age and have lived in the United Kingdom for at least 5 years throughout your life (this does not have to be for the last five years or consecutively - just at least 5 years over the course of your life).

 

Researchers:

Sam Taylor (sjt80@bath.ac.uk)

PhD Student

Department of Psychology

University of Bath

 

Supervised by:

Professor Greg Maio (gm659@bath.ac.uk)

Department of Psychology

University of Bath

 

Ethics Approval Code: 21-252 (Approved by Department of Psychology, University of Bath).

 

If you have any concerns related to your participation in this study, please direct them to Department of Psychology Research Ethics Committee, via psychologyethics@bath.ac.uk.

 

 

Please read the following statements and then answer the questions below to consent to participating in this study:


	I have received enough information about the purpose and nature of this study to make a decision about my participation.
	I understand that I am free to ask any questions at any time and without having to give a reason. I am free to withdraw or discuss my concerns with the researcher, Sam Taylor (sjt80@bath.ac.uk), or their supervisor, Professor Greg Maio (gm659@bath.ac.uk).
	I understand and acknowledge that the investigation is designed to promote scientific knowledge and that the University of Bath will use the data I provide for no other purpose than research.
	I understand that the University of Bath may make the data from all participants publicly available as a set. I understand that this means that the data may be used for purposes not related to this study, but that the conditions on this form under which I have provided the data will still apply and it will not be possible to identify me from these data.
	I understand that I can withdraw from the study (including any data collected in previous sessions) up until the point of randomisation and anonymisation (which will be no more than 4 weeks after the final data collection session). - I consent to taking part in this study.

ProlificID:
What is your Prolific ID? 
Please note that this response should auto-fill with the correct ID.
Gender: What gender do you identify as? - Selected Choice
Gender_4_TEXT: What gender do you identify as? - I do not identify as male, female or non-binary. I identify as: - Text
Age: How old are you in years (e.g. 25)?
Region:
Throughout this survey, you will be asked to consider your thoughts towards three areas and the people within them: your neighbourhood, the wider region (England) or country (Scotland, Wales or Northern Ireland) in which you live, and the United Kingdom as a whole.



When considering your neighbourhood, people may define their neighbourhood in different ways. Please define it in whatever way is meaningful to you, considering the place where your main residence is located and where you would consider your neighbours to be located.



When considering the United Kingdom, consider all of the people who live in all areas of the United Kingdom.



When considering the area in which you live, please look at the map below and select your region, making sure in future questions to consider all of the people who live in that area when prompted. 







Firstly, please confirm which country in the UK or region of England you currently live in (if you are unsure, see the list below marked *). 

If you frequently move between neighbourhoods and regions or countries of the United Kingdom, please select the neighbourhood you identify with the most and select the corresponding region within which that neighbourhood is located. It is important that the neighbourhood you consider is within the country or region you select.
Self_SVS_1:
In the following section you will be presented with a list of values. The main question in this task will be: "Which values are important to you as guiding principles in your life, and which values are less important to you?".

 

 
Use the rating scale below:


	0 means the value is not at all important; it is not relevant as a guiding principle for your life.
	3 means the value is important.
	6 means the value is very important. 


The higher the number, the more important the value is as a guiding principle in your life.


	-1 is for rating any values opposed to the principles that guide you.
	7 is for rating a value of supreme importance as a guiding principle in your life; normally, there are no more than two such values. 


Try to distinguish as much as possible between the values by using all the numbers. You will, of course, need to use numbers more than once.



As a guiding principle in my life, this value is: - Protecting the environment (from destruction or pollution)
